            <title>[FLINK-31346] Batch shuffle IO scheduler does not throw TimeoutException if numRequestedBuffers is greater than 0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-31346</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We currently rely on throw exception to trigger downstream task failover to avoid read buffer request deadlock. But if &lt;tt&gt;numRequestedBuffers&lt;/tt&gt; is greater than 0, IO scheduler does not throw &lt;tt&gt;TimeoutException&lt;/tt&gt;. This will cause a deadlock.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
